baseball <- read.csv('-2013.csv',stringsAsFactors=F)

options(digits = 2)

# 1) bar  ==================================================================
baseball %>% 
  mutate(OPS=+) %>%
  mutate(OPS=round(OPS/,1)) %>% 
  select(,OPS) %>%
  ggplot(aes(x=,y=OPS,fill=)) +
  geom_bar(stat="identity",position="dodge",color="black") +
  geom_text(aes(y=OPS+0.03, label=paste0(OPS,"%")), color='black',size=3) +
  geom_hline(yintercept=seq(0,1,0.125),lty='dashed',size=0.5) +
  theme_bw(base_family='baedal',base_size = 10) +
  theme(axis.title.x = element_blank()) +
  theme(axis.text.x  = element_text(angle=45, hjust=1)) +
  ggtitle('    OPS ') +
  theme(plot.title = element_text(family="baedal",
                                  face = "bold",
                                  hjust = 0.5,
                                  vjust = 2.5,
                                  size = 20, 
                                  color = "black"))

unemployment <- read.csv('2000-2013 __.csv')

ggplot(unemployment_melt,aes(x=,y=,fill=,color=,group=)) +
